Read and follow the canonical context in `docs/ai-context/`.

Priority reading order:
1) `docs/ai-context/README.md`
2) `docs/ai-context/project-overview.md`
3) `docs/ai-context/current-status.md`
4) `docs/ai-context/roadmap-priorities.md`
5) `docs/ai-context/engineering-rules.md`
6) `docs/ai-context/developer-profile.md`
7) `docs/ai-context/decisions-log.md`
8) `docs/CHECKLIST_TESTE_SANDBOX_PLAY.md` (Android Play sandbox / internal test QA)
9) `docs/play-store-listing-dulang.md` (Play Store listing copy — policy-aligned)
10) `docs/PASSO_A_PASSO_FASE2_ASSINATURA_LEIGO.md` (ops: lojas + assinatura + PIN)

Do not create a parallel source of truth in tool-specific files.
Tool-specific guidance should remain minimal and point back to `docs/ai-context/`.

**Git:** assistants must not `git commit` or `git push` without explicit operator authorization (any branch; see `docs/ai-context/engineering-rules.md`).

When the user or project material is in Portuguese, write **Brazilian Portuguese (pt-BR)** only—not European Portuguese (pt-PT). This is enforced in **`portugues-brasil.mdc`** (this folder) **and** in `docs/ai-context/developer-profile.md` / `engineering-rules.md`: same premise in **rules** and **canonical docs**.
